node.text:
The iconically classy BMW 328 - Sir Stirling Moss' first race car - giving the Goodwood Revival a serious dose of 1930’s charm. 

An unbeatable racer in its day, the 328 inspired British car company Frazer-Nash to buy the rights to the car on the UK market, where it, of course, became a roaring success with both amateurs and professionals alike! Moss' father bought this one,  and the rest is history...

(📸@mateboerphotography)
@goodwoodrevival
